<article class="prose lg:prose-lg max-w-none mb-8">
  <h1>Submit Your Entry</h1>

  <p>Submit an Open Education Week entry in two easy steps: </p>

  <div class="flex justify-evenly mb-10 flex-col lg:flex-row gap-6">
    <div class="rounded bg-white lg:shadow lg:w-1/3 pt-4 pb-10 px-10 flex flex-col justify-center items-center gap-4">
      {{svg-jar "step1" class="h-auto inline-block"}}
      <p class="text-sm">Tell us about yourself and your institution/organization.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded bg-white lg:shadow lg:w-1/3 pt-4 pb-10 px-10 flex flex-col justify-center items-center gap-4">
      {{svg-jar "step2" class="h-auto inline-block"}}
      <p class="text-sm">Describe your contribution, provide a link, and upload an image.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div
    class="p-4 lg:px-8 lg:py-4 bg-green-100 flex flex-col gap-4 border border-green-400 border-1 lg:rounded-2xl mb-10">
    <p>Additional information regarding your submission:</p>
    <CheckText>All entries must be openly licensed.</CheckText>
    <CheckText>Once your submission is approved you will receive a confirmation email and your entry will be
      displayed on the OE Week website.
    </CheckText>
    <CheckText>For edits and/or updates in your submission, please use the link provided on the confirmation email.
    </CheckText>
    <CheckText>The data collected by the OE Global through this form is specifically used for OE Week operational
      purposes.</CheckText>
    <CheckText>For questions or comments, please contact us at
      <a href="mailto:info@openeducationweek.org" class="inline-block">info@openeducationweek.org</a>.
    </CheckText>
  </div>

</article>

<LinkTo @route="submit.general" class="button-main">Get Started</LinkTo>